#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn14:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 14"
msgstr "Long Discourses 14"

# The title is not easy to translate. There is no reason to think apadāna was yet in use as a standard term for "story of past lives"; rather, such usage derived from here. Chinese versions of the text have completely different titles: "Seven Buddhas", "The Great Root", "Vipassi Buddha", "The Lineage of the Seven Past Buddhas". Only the second of these might relate to the Pali. The sense seems to have been "(story about) reaping results of deeds".
#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn14:2.1"
msgid "Mahāpadānasutta"
msgstr "The Harvest of Deeds"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.1"
msgid "1. Pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttakathā"
msgstr "On Past Lives"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.1"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.1"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:4.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

# Kareri doesn't seem to have a recognized English name.
msgctxt "dn14:4.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme "
"karerikuṭikāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī, in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery, in the hut by the <i>kareri</i> tree."

msgctxt "dn14:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ "
"karerimaṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttā "
"dhammī kathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Then after the meal, on return from alms-round, several senior mendicants "
"sat together in the pavilion by the <i>kareri</i> tree and this Dhamma talk "
"on the subject of past lives came up among them."

msgctxt "dn14:4.4"
msgid "“itipi pubbenivāso, itipi pubbenivāso”ti."
msgstr "“So it was in a past life; such it was in a past life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:5.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho bhagavā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya tesaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha heard that "
"discussion among the mendicants."

msgctxt "dn14:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena karerimaṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "So he got up from his seat and went to the pavillion,"

msgctxt "dn14:5.3"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi, nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out and addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn14:5.4"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā;"
msgstr "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? "

msgctxt "dn14:5.5"
msgid "kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?"
msgstr "What conversation was unfinished?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding:"

msgctxt "dn14:6.2"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ "
"karerimaṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttā "
"dhammī kathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:6.3"
msgid "‘itipi pubbenivāso itipi pubbenivāso’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā."
msgstr "“This is the conversation that was unfinished"

msgctxt "dn14:6.5"
msgid "Atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti."
msgstr "when the Buddha arrived.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Iccheyyātha no tumhe, bhikkhave, pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"sotun”ti?"
msgstr "“Would you like to hear a Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives?”"

msgctxt "dn14:7.2"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo;"
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:7.3"
msgid "etassa, sugata, kālo;"
msgstr " "

#. VAR: bhagavato sutvā → bhagavato vacanaṃ sutvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:7.4"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyya, bhagavato sutvā "
"bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let the Buddha give a Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "dn14:7.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha sādhukaṃ manasi karotha bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn14:7.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn14:7.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:  "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.4"></a>
#. VAR: ekanavutikappe → ekanavuto kappo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Ito so, bhikkhave, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke udapādi."
msgstr ""
"“Ninety-one eons ago, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, perfected and "
"fully awakened."

#. VAR: ekatiṃse kappe → ekatiṃso kappo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:8.2"
msgid ""
"Ito so, bhikkhave, ekatiṃse kappe yaṃ sikhī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke udapādi."
msgstr ""
"Thirty-one eons ago, the Buddha Sikhī arose in the world, perfected and "
"fully awakened."

msgctxt "dn14:8.3"
msgid ""
"Tasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, ekatiṃse kappe vessabhū bhagavā arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho loke udapādi."
msgstr ""
"In the same thirty-first eon, the Buddha Vessabhū arose in the world, "
"perfected and fully awakened."

#. VAR: Imasmiññeva → imasmiṃ yeva (km, pts1) | imasmiṃ (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn14:8.4"
msgid ""
"Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho loke udapādi."
msgstr "In the present fortunate eon, the Buddhas Kakusandha,"

msgctxt "dn14:8.5"
msgid ""
"Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe koṇāgamano bhagavā arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho loke udapādi."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana,"

msgctxt "dn14:8.6"
msgid ""
"Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho loke udapādi."
msgstr "and Kassapa arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened."

msgctxt "dn14:8.7"
msgid ""
"Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe ahaṃ etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke uppanno."
msgstr ""
"And in the present fortunate eon, I have arisen in the world, perfected and "
"fully awakened."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.5"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:9.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, "
"khattiyakule udapādi."
msgstr "The Buddhas Vipassī,"

msgctxt "dn14:9.2"
msgid ""
"Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, "
"khattiyakule udapādi."
msgstr "Sikhī,"

msgctxt "dn14:9.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, "
"khattiyakule udapādi."
msgstr "and Vessabhū were born as aristocrats into an aristocrat family."

msgctxt "dn14:9.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, "
"brāhmaṇakule udapādi."
msgstr "The Buddhas Kakusandha,"

msgctxt "dn14:9.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, "
"brāhmaṇakule udapādi."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana,"

msgctxt "dn14:9.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, "
"brāhmaṇakule udapādi."
msgstr "and Kassapa were born as brahmins into a brahmin family."

msgctxt "dn14:9.7"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosiṃ, "
"khattiyakule uppanno."
msgstr "I was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:10.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi."
msgstr "Koṇḍañña was the clan of Vipassī,"

msgctxt "dn14:10.2"
msgid "Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi."
msgstr "Sikhī,"

msgctxt "dn14:10.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi."
msgstr "and Vessabhū."

msgctxt "dn14:10.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi."
msgstr "Kassapa was the clan of Kakusandha,"

msgctxt "dn14:10.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana,"

msgctxt "dn14:10.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi."
msgstr "and Kassapa."

msgctxt "dn14:10.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho gotamo gottena ahosiṃ."
msgstr "Gotama is my clan."

# Both RD and MW say this is the lifespan in that eon. And it is true that this is the normal usage of ayuppamana. However, in such cases the subject in genitive is given as plural, to denote the entire generation, etc. Here it is singular, and specifies only Vipassi. Sure, it's likely that this would have been typical, but I don't think that's what the text is saying. Note that when the Buddha speaks of his own life, he uses a different phrasing. If ayuppamana here referred to the lifespan of the current generation, there would be no reason for the Buddha to not apply it to himself. But if it means that of the individual, then it makes sense why he would shift to a more indirect statement.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:11.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Vipassī lived for 80,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.2"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"sattativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Sikhī lived for 70,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"saṭṭhivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Vessabhū lived for 60,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"cattālīsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Kakusandha lived for 40,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"tiṃsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana lived for 30,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"vīsativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "Kassapa lived for 20,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:11.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ;"
msgstr "For me these days the life-span is short, brief, and fleeting."

msgctxt "dn14:11.8"
msgid "yo ciraṃ jīvati, so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo."
msgstr "A long-lived person lives for a century or a little more."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:12.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Vipassī was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree."

# puṇḍarīka is the white lotus; Comm says this is setamba, which must have been a tree with lotus-like flowers, I guess.
msgctxt "dn14:12.2"
msgid ""
"Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho puṇḍarīkassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Sikhī was awakened at the root of a white-mango tree."

msgctxt "dn14:12.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sālassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Vessabhū was awakened at the root of a <i>sal</i> tree."

msgctxt "dn14:12.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sirīsassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Kakusandha was awakened at the root of an acacia tree."

msgctxt "dn14:12.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho udumbarassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana was awakened at the root of a cluster fig tree."

msgctxt "dn14:12.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nigrodhassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "Kassapa was awakened at the root of a banyan tree."

# peepul seems to be the most common of the many words for the Bodhi tree.
msgctxt "dn14:12.7"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho assatthassa mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "I was awakened at the root of a peepul tree."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.9"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:13.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma "
"sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "Vipassī had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa."

msgctxt "dn14:13.2"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa abhibhūsambhavaṃ "
"nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "Sikhī had a fine pair of chief disciples named Abhibhū and Sambhava."

msgctxt "dn14:13.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa soṇuttaraṃ nāma "
"sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "Vessabhū had a fine pair of chief disciples named Soṇa and Uttara."

msgctxt "dn14:13.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"vidhurasañjīvaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Kakusandha had a fine pair of chief disciples named Vidhura and Sañjīva."

msgctxt "dn14:13.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhiyyosuttaraṃ "
"nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "Koṇāgmana had a fine pair of chief disciples named Bhiyyosa and Uttara."

msgctxt "dn14:13.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tissabhāradvājaṃ "
"nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "Kassapa had a fine pair of chief disciples named Tissa and Bhāradvāja."

msgctxt "dn14:13.7"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ "
"bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "I have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

# Both RD and MW have "assemblies", which is a little misleading. It doesn't refer to permanent groupings, but events.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:14.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Vipassī had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:14.2"
msgid ""
"Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi "
"asītibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—"

msgctxt "dn14:14.3"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:15.1"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Sikhī had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:15.2"
msgid ""
"Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto "
"ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi "
"sattatibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "one of 100,000, one of 80,000, and one of 70,000—"

msgctxt "dn14:15.3"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:16.1"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Vessabhū had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:16.2"
msgid ""
"Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto "
"ahosi sattatibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi "
"saṭṭhibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "one of 80,000, one of 70,000, and one of 60,000—"

msgctxt "dn14:16.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:17.1"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipāto ahosi cattālīsabhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "Kakusandha had one gathering of disciples—40,000"

msgctxt "dn14:17.2"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:18.1"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipāto ahosi tiṃsabhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had one gathering of disciples—30,000"

msgctxt "dn14:18.2"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:19.1"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipāto ahosi vīsatibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "Kassapa had one gathering of disciples—20,000"

msgctxt "dn14:19.2"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:20.1"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aḍḍhateḷasāni "
"bhikkhusatāni."
msgstr "I have had one gathering of disciples—1,250 "

msgctxt "dn14:20.2"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva "
"khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "mendicants who had ended their defilements."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:21.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Vipassī had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka."

msgctxt "dn14:21.2"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khemaṅkaro nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Sikhī had as chief attendant a mendicant named Khemaṅkara."

msgctxt "dn14:21.3"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa upasanto nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Vessabhū had as chief attendant a mendicant named Upasanta."

msgctxt "dn14:21.4"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa buddhijo nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Kakusandha had as chief attendant a mendicant named Buddhija."

msgctxt "dn14:21.5"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sotthijo nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had as chief attendant a mendicant named Sotthija."

msgctxt "dn14:21.6"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sabbamitto nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "Kassapa had as chief attendant a mendicant named Sabbamitta."

msgctxt "dn14:21.7"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi ānando nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "I have as chief attendant a mendicant named Ānanda."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.12"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:22.1"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma "
"rājā pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Vipassī’s father was King Bandhuma,"

#. VAR: janetti → janettī (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:22.2"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī,"

msgctxt "dn14:22.3"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:23.1"
msgid ""
"Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa aruṇo nāma rājā "
"pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Sikhī’s father was King Aruṇa,"

msgctxt "dn14:23.2"
msgid "Pabhāvatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Pabhāvatī,"

msgctxt "dn14:23.3"
msgid "Aruṇassa rañño aruṇavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and their capital city was named Aruṇavatī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
#. VAR: suppatito nāma → suppatīto nāma (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:24.1"
msgid ""
"Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa suppatito nāma "
"rājā pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Vessabhū’s father was King Suppatīta,"

#. VAR: Vassavatī nāma → yasavatī nāma (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:24.2"
msgid "Vassavatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Vassavatī,"

msgctxt "dn14:24.3"
msgid "Suppatitassa rañño anomaṃ nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and their capital city was named Suppatīta."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:25.1"
msgid ""
"Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa aggidatto nāma "
"brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Kakusandha’s father was the brahmin Aggidatta,"

msgctxt "dn14:25.2"
msgid "Visākhā nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Visākhā."

msgctxt "dn14:25.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena khemo nāma rājā ahosi."
msgstr "At that time the king was Khema,"

msgctxt "dn14:25.4"
msgid "Khemassa rañño khemavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "whose capital city was named Khemavatī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:26.1"
msgid ""
"Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa yaññadatto "
"nāma brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Koṇāgamana’s father was the brahmin Yaññadatta,"

msgctxt "dn14:26.2"
msgid "Uttarā nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Uttarā."

msgctxt "dn14:26.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena sobho nāma rājā ahosi."
msgstr "At that time the king was Sobha,"

msgctxt "dn14:26.4"
msgid "Sobhassa rañño sobhavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "whose capital city was named Sobhavatī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
#. VAR: nāma → kiṃkī nāma (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:27.1"
msgid ""
"Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa brahmadatto nāma "
"brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Kassapa’s father was the brahmin Brahmadatta,"

msgctxt "dn14:27.2"
msgid "Dhanavatī nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Dhanavatī."

msgctxt "dn14:27.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kikī nāma rājā ahosi."
msgstr "At that time the king was Kikī,"

msgctxt "dn14:27.4"
msgid "Kikissa rañño bārāṇasī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "whose capital city was named Benares."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:28.1"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi suddhodano nāma rājā pitā ahosi."
msgstr "My father is King Suddhodana,"

msgctxt "dn14:28.2"
msgid "Māyā nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "my birth mother was Queen Māyā,"

msgctxt "dn14:28.3"
msgid "Kapilavatthu nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosī”ti."
msgstr "and our capital city was Kapilavatthu.”"

msgctxt "dn14:28.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn14:28.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his "
"dwelling."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.13"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:29.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato ayamantarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants discussed among themselves:"

msgctxt "dn14:29.2"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, reverends, it’s amazing, the power and might of a Realized "
"One!"

msgctxt "dn14:29.3"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume "
"pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarissati, nāmatopi "
"anussarissati, gottatopi anussarissati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarissati, "
"sāvakayugatopi anussarissati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarissati:"
msgstr ""
"For he is able to recollect the caste, names, clans, life-span, chief "
"disciples, and gatherings of disciples of the Buddhas of the past who have "
"become completely extinguished, cut off proliferation, cut off the track, "
"finished off the cycle, and transcended suffering."

msgctxt "dn14:29.4"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"He knows the caste they were born in, and also their names, clans, conduct, "
"teaching, wisdom, meditation, and freedom."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:30.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, tathāgatasseva nu kho esā dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, "
"yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute "
"chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi "
"anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi "
"anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati:"
msgstr ""
"It is because the Realized One has thoroughly penetrated the principle of "
"the teachings that he can recollect all these things?"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:30.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti, "
"udāhu devatā tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe "
"parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte "
"jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, "
"āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi "
"anussarati:"
msgstr "Or did deities tell him?”"

msgctxt "dn14:30.3"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:30.4"
msgid "Ayañca hidaṃ tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antarākathā vippakatā hoti."
msgstr "But this conversation among those mendicants was left unfinished."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:31.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena karerimaṇḍalamāḷo "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of solitude and went to the "
"pavilion by the <i>kareri</i> tree,"

msgctxt "dn14:31.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "dn14:31.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn14:31.4"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā;"
msgstr "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? "

msgctxt "dn14:31.5"
msgid "kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?"
msgstr "What conversation was unfinished?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:32.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding:"

msgctxt "dn14:32.2"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato ayaṃ antarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.3"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.4"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume "
"pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarissati, nāmatopi "
"anussarissati, gottatopi anussarissati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarissati, "
"sāvakayugatopi anussarissati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarissati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.5"
msgid ""
"“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.6"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, tathāgatasseva nu kho esā dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, "
"yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute "
"chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi "
"anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi "
"anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.7"
msgid ""
"“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.8"
msgid ""
"Udāhu devatā tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe "
"parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte "
"jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, "
"āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi "
"anussarati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.9"
msgid ""
"“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:32.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This was our conversation that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:33.1"
msgid ""
"“Tathāgatassevesā, bhikkhave, dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, yassā dhammadhātuyā "
"suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce "
"chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, "
"nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, "
"sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati:"
msgstr ""
"“It is because the Realized One has thoroughly penetrated the principle of "
"the teachings that he can recollect all these things."

msgctxt "dn14:33.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:33.3"
msgid ""
"Devatāpi tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe "
"parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte "
"jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, "
"āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi "
"anussarati:"
msgstr "And the deities also told me."

msgctxt "dn14:33.4"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā "
"evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:34.1"
msgid ""
"Iccheyyātha no tumhe, bhikkhave, bhiyyoso mattāya pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ "
"dhammiṃ kathaṃ sotun”ti?"
msgstr "Would you like to hear more Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives?”"

msgctxt "dn14:34.2"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo;"
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "dn14:34.3"
msgid "etassa, sugata, kālo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:34.4"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā bhiyyoso mattāya pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"kareyya, bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let the Buddha give more Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "dn14:34.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

msgctxt "dn14:34.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn14:34.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.16"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:35.1"
msgid ""
"“Ito so, bhikkhave, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke udapādi."
msgstr ""
"“Ninety-one eons ago, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, perfected and "
"fully awakened."

msgctxt "dn14:35.2"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, "
"khattiyakule udapādi."
msgstr "He was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family."

msgctxt "dn14:35.3"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi."
msgstr "His clan was Koṇḍañña."

msgctxt "dn14:35.4"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "He lived for 80,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:35.5"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle "
"abhisambuddho."
msgstr "He was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree."

msgctxt "dn14:35.6"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma "
"sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "He had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa."

msgctxt "dn14:35.7"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "He had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:35.8"
msgid ""
"Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi "
"asītibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr "one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—"

msgctxt "dn14:35.9"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo "
"sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements."

msgctxt "dn14:35.10"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma "
"bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "He had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka."

msgctxt "dn14:35.11"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma "
"rājā pitā ahosi."
msgstr "His father was King Bandhuma,"

msgctxt "dn14:35.12"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī,"

msgctxt "dn14:35.13"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:36.1"
msgid "2. Bodhisattadhammatā"
msgstr "What’s Normal For One Intent on Awakening"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:37.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto tusitā kāyā cavitvā sato sampajāno "
"mātukucchiṃ okkami."
msgstr ""
"When Vipassī, the being intent on awakening, passed away from the group of "
"Joyful Gods, he was conceived in his mother’s womb, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "dn14:37.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:38.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto tusitā kāyā cavitvā mātukucchiṃ "
"okkamati."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening passes away from the "
"group of Joyful Gods, he’s conceived in his mother’s womb."

msgctxt "dn14:38.2"
msgid ""
"Atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ "
"devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population "
"with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent "
"light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods."

msgctxt "dn14:38.3"
msgid ""
"Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā, yatthapime "
"candimasūriyā evaṃmahiddhikā evaṃmahānubhāvā ābhāya nānubhonti, tatthapi "
"appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that "
"even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no "
"impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory "
"of the gods."

msgctxt "dn14:38.4"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā, tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:"
msgstr ""
"And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light:"

msgctxt "dn14:38.5"
msgid "‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti."
msgstr "‘So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!’"

msgctxt "dn14:38.6"
msgid "Ayañca dasasahassī lokadhātu saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"And this galaxy shakes and rocks and trembles. And an immeasurable, "
"magnificent light appears in the world, surpassing the glory of the gods."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:38.7"
msgid ""
"Appamāṇo ca uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:38.8"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
#. VAR: catuddisaṃ → cātuddisaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:39.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, cattāro "
"naṃ devaputtā catuddisaṃ rakkhāya upagacchanti:"
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his "
"mother’s belly, four deities approach to guard the four directions,"

msgctxt "dn14:39.2"
msgid ""
"‘mā naṃ bodhisattaṃ vā bodhisattamātaraṃ vā manusso vā amanusso vā koci vā "
"viheṭhesī’ti."
msgstr ""
"so that no human or non-human or anyone at all shall harm the being intent "
"on awakening or his mother."

msgctxt "dn14:39.3"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.18"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:40.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, pakatiyā "
"sīlavatī bodhisattamātā hoti, viratā pāṇātipātā, viratā adinnādānā, viratā "
"kāmesumicchācārā, viratā musāvādā, viratā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his "
"mother’s belly, she becomes naturally ethical. She refrains from killing "
"living creatures, stealing, sexual misconduct, lying, and alcoholic drinks "
"that cause negligence."

msgctxt "dn14:40.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr "This normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:41.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na "
"bodhisattamātu purisesu mānasaṃ uppajjati kāmaguṇūpasaṃhitaṃ, anatikkamanīyā "
"ca bodhisattamātā hoti kenaci purisena rattacittena."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his "
"mother’s belly, she no longer feels sexual desire for men, and she cannot be "
"violated by a man of lustful intent."

msgctxt "dn14:41.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:42.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, lābhinī "
"bodhisattamātā hoti pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his "
"mother’s belly, she obtains the five kinds of sensual stimulation and amuses "
"herself, supplied and provided with them."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:42.2"
msgid "Sā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricāreti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:42.3"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.21"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:43.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na "
"bodhisattamātu kocideva ābādho uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his "
"mother’s belly, no afflictions beset her."

msgctxt "dn14:43.2"
msgid ""
"Sukhinī bodhisattamātā hoti akilantakāyā, bodhisattañca bodhisattamātā "
"tirokucchigataṃ passati sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"She’s happy and free of bodily fatigue. And she sees the being intent on "
"awakening in her womb, complete with all his various parts, not deficient in "
"any faculty."

msgctxt "dn14:43.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato "
"accho vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, "
"with expert workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all "
"good qualities. "

#. VAR: Tatrāssa → tatra yaṃ (bj) | tatrassa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:43.4"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssa suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"And it was strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown."

msgctxt "dn14:43.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso hatthe karitvā paccavekkheyya:"
msgstr ""
"And someone with good eyesight were to take it in their hand and examine it:"

msgctxt "dn14:43.6"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho "
"vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno."
msgstr ""
"‘This beryl gem is naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, with expert "
"workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all good "
"qualities. "

msgctxt "dn14:43.7"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ "
"vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And it’s strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.’"

msgctxt "dn14:43.8"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na "
"bodhisattamātu kocideva ābādho uppajjati, sukhinī bodhisattamātā hoti "
"akilantakāyā, bodhisattañca bodhisattamātā tirokucchigataṃ passati "
"sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So too, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s "
"belly, no afflictions beset her. She’s happy and free of bodily fatigue. And "
"she sees the being intent on awakening in her womb, complete with all his "
"various parts, not deficient in any faculty."

msgctxt "dn14:43.9"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:44.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, sattāhajāte bodhisatte bodhisattamātā kālaṃ karoti "
"tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, seven days after the being intent on awakening is born, "
"his mother passes away and is reborn in the group of Joyful Gods."

msgctxt "dn14:44.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:45.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yathā aññā itthikā nava vā dasa vā māse gabbhaṃ "
"kucchinā pariharitvā vijāyanti, na hevaṃ bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, while other women carry the infant in the womb for nine or "
"ten months before giving birth, not so the mother of the being intent on "
"awakening."

msgctxt "dn14:45.2"
msgid "Daseva māsāni bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā kucchinā pariharitvā vijāyati."
msgstr "She gives birth after exactly ten months."

msgctxt "dn14:45.3"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:46.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yathā aññā itthikā nisinnā vā nipannā vā vijāyanti, "
"na hevaṃ bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, while other women give birth while sitting or lying down, "
"not so the mother of the being intent on awakening."

msgctxt "dn14:46.2"
msgid "Ṭhitāva bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati."
msgstr "She only gives birth standing up."

msgctxt "dn14:46.3"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.25"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:47.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, devā "
"paṭhamaṃ paṭiggaṇhanti, pacchā manussā."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’"
"s womb, gods receive him first, then humans."

msgctxt "dn14:47.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(11)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:48.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, appattova "
"bodhisatto pathaviṃ hoti, cattāro naṃ devaputtā paṭiggahetvā mātu purato "
"ṭhapenti:"
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’"
"s womb, before he reaches the ground, four deities receive him and place him "
"before his mother, saying:"

msgctxt "dn14:48.2"
msgid "‘attamanā, devi, hohi;"
msgstr "‘Rejoice, O Queen!"

msgctxt "dn14:48.3"
msgid "mahesakkho te putto uppanno’ti."
msgstr "An illustrious child is born to you.’"

msgctxt "dn14:48.4"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(12)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.27"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.15"></a>
#. VAR: udena → uddena (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | udarena (katthaci)
#. VAR: asucinā suddho → visuddho (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:49.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova "
"nikkhamati amakkhito udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito "
"kenaci asucinā suddho visado."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’"
"s womb, he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any "
"other kind of impurity, pure and clean."

msgctxt "dn14:49.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, maṇiratanaṃ kāsike vatthe nikkhittaṃ neva maṇiratanaṃ "
"kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ makkheti, nāpi kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ maṇiratanaṃ makkheti."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a jewel-treasure was placed on a cloth from Kāsī. The jewel would "
"not soil the cloth, nor would the cloth soil the jewel."

msgctxt "dn14:49.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn14:49.4"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ suddhattā."
msgstr "Because of the cleanliness of them both."

msgctxt "dn14:49.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova "
"nikkhamati amakkhito, udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito "
"kenaci asucinā suddho visado."
msgstr ""
"So too, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, "
"he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any other "
"kind of impurity, pure and clean."

msgctxt "dn14:49.6"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(13)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:50.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, dve "
"udakassa dhārā antalikkhā pātubhavanti—"
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’"
"s womb, two streams of water appear in the sky,"

msgctxt "dn14:50.2"
msgid "ekā sītassa ekā uṇhassa yena bodhisattassa udakakiccaṃ karonti mātu ca."
msgstr ""
"one cool, one warm, for bathing the being intent on awakening and his "
"mother.’"

msgctxt "dn14:50.3"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(14)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.29"></a>
#. VAR: uttarābhimukho → uttare­nābhi­mukho (s1-3, km) uttarenamukho (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:51.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, sampatijāto bodhisatto samehi pādehi patiṭṭhahitvā "
"uttarābhimukho sattapadavītihārena gacchati setamhi chatte anudhāriyamāne, "
"sabbā ca disā anuviloketi, āsabhiṃ vācaṃ bhāsati ‘aggohamasmi lokassa, "
"jeṭṭhohamasmi lokassa, seṭṭhohamasmi lokassa, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni "
"punabbhavo’ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, as soon as he’s born, the being intent on awakening stands "
"firm with his own feet on the ground. Facing north, he takes seven strides "
"with a white parasol held above him, surveys all quarters, and makes this "
"dramatic statement: ‘I am the foremost in the world! I am the eldest in the "
"world! I am the best in the world! This is my last birth. Now there are no "
"more future lives.’"

msgctxt "dn14:51.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(15)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:52.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, atha "
"sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya "
"appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati, atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’"
"s womb then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population "
"with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent "
"light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods."

msgctxt "dn14:52.2"
msgid ""
"Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā, yatthapime "
"candimasūriyā evaṃmahiddhikā evaṃmahānubhāvā ābhāya nānubhonti, tatthapi "
"appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that "
"even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no "
"impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory "
"of the gods."

msgctxt "dn14:52.3"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā, tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti:"
msgstr ""
"And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light:"

msgctxt "dn14:52.4"
msgid "‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti."
msgstr "‘So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!’"

msgctxt "dn14:52.5"
msgid ""
"Ayañca dasasahassī lokadhātu saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati appamāṇo "
"ca uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And this galaxy shakes and rocks and trembles. And an immeasurable, "
"magnificent light appears in the world, surpassing the glory of the gods."

msgctxt "dn14:52.6"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. <span class=\"brnum\">(16)</span>"
msgstr "This is normal in such a case."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:53.1"
msgid "3. Dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇā"
msgstr "The Thirty-Two Marks of a Great Man"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.31"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.16"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:54.1"
msgid ""
"Jāte kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassimhi kumāre bandhumato rañño paṭivedesuṃ:"
msgstr "When Prince Vipassī was born, they announced it to King Bandhumata:"

#. VAR: deva → deva te (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:54.2"
msgid "‘putto te, deva, jāto, taṃ devo passatū’ti."
msgstr "‘Sire, your son is born! Let your majesty examine him!’"

msgctxt "dn14:54.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassiṃ kumāraṃ, disvā nemitte "
"brāhmaṇe āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the king had examined the prince, he had the brahmin soothsayers "
"summoned and said to them:"

msgctxt "dn14:54.4"
msgid "‘passantu bhonto nemittā brāhmaṇā kumāran’ti."
msgstr "‘Gentlemen, please examine the prince.’"

msgctxt "dn14:54.5"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃsu kho, bhikkhave, nemittā brāhmaṇā vipassiṃ kumāraṃ, disvā "
"bandhumantaṃ rājānaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When they had examined him they said to the king:"

msgctxt "dn14:54.6"
msgid ""
"‘attamano, deva, hohi, mahesakkho te putto uppanno, lābhā te, mahārāja, "
"suladdhaṃ te, mahārāja, yassa te kule evarūpo putto uppanno."
msgstr ""
"‘Rejoice, O King! An illustrious son is born to you. You are fortunate, so "
"very fortunate, to have a son such as this born in this family!’"

msgctxt "dn14:54.7"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi, deva, kumāro dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato, yehi "
"samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā."
msgstr ""
"For the prince has the thirty-two marks of a great man. A great man who "
"possesses these has only two possible destinies, no other."

msgctxt "dn14:54.8"
msgid ""
"Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto "
"vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato."
msgstr ""
"If he stays at home he becomes a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and "
"principled king. His dominion extends to all four sides, he achieves "
"stability in the country, and he possesses the seven treasures."

msgctxt "dn14:54.9"
msgid "Tassimāni sattaratanāni bhavanti."
msgstr "He has the following seven treasures:"

msgctxt "dn14:54.10"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:54.11"
msgid ""
"cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ "
"gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and "
"the counselor as the seventh treasure."

msgctxt "dn14:54.12"
msgid ""
"Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā."
msgstr ""
"He has over a thousand sons who are valiant and heroic, crushing the armies "
"of his enemies."

msgctxt "dn14:54.13"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya "
"ajjhāvasati."
msgstr ""
"After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigns by principle, without rod "
"or sword."

msgctxt "dn14:54.14"
msgid ""
"Sace kho pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke "
"vivaṭacchado."
msgstr ""
"But if he goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, he becomes a "
"perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the "
"world."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.32"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:55.1"
msgid ""
