"perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the "
"world.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:89.1"
msgid "4. Vipassīsamaññā"
msgstr "How He Came to be Known as Vipassī"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.20"></a>
#. VAR: acchādāpetvā → acchādetvā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:90.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā nemitte brāhmaṇe ahatehi vatthehi "
"acchādāpetvā sabbakāmehi santappesi."
msgstr ""
"Then King Bandhuma had the brahmin soothsayers dressed in fresh clothes and "
"satisfied all their needs."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.34"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:90.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa dhātiyo upaṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr "Then the king appointed nurses for Prince Vipassī."

msgctxt "dn14:90.3"
msgid ""
"Aññā khīraṃ pāyenti, aññā nhāpenti, aññā dhārenti, aññā aṅkena pariharanti."
msgstr ""
"Some suckled him, some bathed him, some held him, and some carried him on "
"their hip."

msgctxt "dn14:90.4"
msgid ""
"Jātassa kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa setacchattaṃ dhārayittha "
"divā ceva rattiñca:"
msgstr ""
"From when he was born, a white parasol was held over him night and day, with "
"the thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:90.5"
msgid "‘mā naṃ sītaṃ vā uṇhaṃ vā tiṇaṃ vā rajo vā ussāvo vā bādhayitthā’ti."
msgstr "‘Don’t let cold, heat, grass, dust, or damp bother him.’"

msgctxt "dn14:90.6"
msgid ""
"Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahuno janassa piyo ahosi manāpo."
msgstr "He was dear and beloved by many people,"

msgctxt "dn14:90.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā bahuno janassa "
"piyaṃ manāpaṃ;"
msgstr "like a blue water lily, or a pink or white lotus."

msgctxt "dn14:90.8"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahuno janassa piyo ahosi manāpo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:90.9"
msgid "Svāssudaṃ aṅkeneva aṅkaṃ parihariyati."
msgstr "He was always passed from hip to hip."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.35"></a>
#. VAR: kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca → kumāro brahmassaro
#. mañjussaro ca (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:91.1"
msgid ""
"Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca ahosi vaggussaro ca "
"madhurassaro ca pemaniyassaro ca."
msgstr ""
"From when he was born, his voice was charming, graceful, sweet, and lovely."

msgctxt "dn14:91.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, himavante pabbate karavīkā nāma sakuṇajāti mañjussarā "
"ca vaggussarā ca madhurassarā ca pemaniyassarā ca;"
msgstr "It was as sweet as the song of cuckoo-bird found in the Himalayas."

msgctxt "dn14:91.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca ahosi vaggussaro ca "
"madhurassaro ca pemaniyassaro ca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.36"></a>
#. VAR: yena sudaṃ → yena dūraṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:92.1"
msgid ""
"Jātassa kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa kammavipākajaṃ dibbacakkhu "
"pāturahosi yena sudaṃ samantā yojanaṃ passati divā ceva rattiñca."
msgstr ""
"From when he was born, Prince Vipassī had the power of clairvoyance which "
"manifested as a result of past deeds. He could see for a league all around "
"both by day and by night."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="87"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.37"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:93.1"
msgid ""
"Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro animisanto pekkhati seyyathāpi devā "
"tāvatiṃsā."
msgstr "And he was unblinkingly watchful, like the gods of the Thirty-Three."

#. VAR: Animisanto kumāro pekkhatī’ti kho, bhikkhave → jātassa kho pana
#. bhikkhave (s1-3) | animmissantā pekkhāti evameva kho bhikkheve (km) |
#. jātassa kho pana bhikkhave (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:93.2"
msgid ""
"‘Animisanto kumāro pekkhatī’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa ‘vipassī "
"vipassī’ tveva samaññā udapādi."
msgstr ""
"And because it was said that he was unblinkingly watchful, he came to be "
"known as ‘Vipassī’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="88"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.21"></a>
#. VAR: atthakaraṇe → aṭṭakaraṇe (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:94.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā atthakaraṇe nisinno vipassiṃ kumāraṃ aṅke "
"nisīdāpetvā atthe anusāsati."
msgstr ""
"Then while King Bandhuma was sitting in judgement, he’d sit Prince Vipassī "
"in his lap and explain the case to him."

# MW is wrong here.
#. VAR: ñāyena → ñāṇena (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:94.2"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro pituaṅke nisinno viceyya viceyya "
"atthe panāyati ñāyena."
msgstr ""
"And sitting there in his father’s lap, Vipassī would thoroughly consider the "
"case and draw a conclusion using a logical procedure."

msgctxt "dn14:94.3"
msgid ""
"Viceyya viceyya kumāro atthe panāyati ñāyenāti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa "
"kumārassa bhiyyoso mattāya ‘vipassī vipassī’ tveva samaññā udapādi."
msgstr "So this was all the more reason for him to be known as ‘Vipassī’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="89"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.38"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:95.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa tayo pāsāde "
"kārāpesi, ekaṃ vassikaṃ ekaṃ hemantikaṃ ekaṃ gimhikaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Then King Bandhuma had three three stilt longhouses built for him—one for "
"the winter, one for the summer, and one for the rainy season,"

msgctxt "dn14:95.2"
msgid "pañca kāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr "and provided him with the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

#. VAR: Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro vassike pāsāde cattāro māse →
#. vassike pāsāde vassike cattāro māse (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:95.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro vassike pāsāde cattāro māse "
"nippurisehi tūriyehi paricārayamāno na heṭṭhāpāsādaṃ orohatīti."
msgstr ""
"Prince Vipassī stayed in a stilt longhouse without coming downstairs for the "
"four months of the rainy season, where he was entertained by musicians—none "
"of them men."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn14:96.1"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:97.1"
msgid "5. Jiṇṇapurisa"
msgstr "The Old Man"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="90"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.1"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:98.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ "
"bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many thousand years had passed, Prince Vipassī addressed his "
"charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:98.2"
msgid ""
"‘yojehi, samma sārathi, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma "
"subhūmidassanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My dear charioteer, harness the finest chariots. We will go to a park and "
"see the scenery.’"

msgctxt "dn14:98.3"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā "
"bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojetvā vipassissa kumārassa paṭivedesi:"
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, sir,’ replied the charioteer. He harnessed the chariots and informed "
"the prince:"

msgctxt "dn14:98.4"
msgid ""
"‘yuttāni kho te, deva, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti."
msgstr "‘Sire, the finest chariots are harnessed. Please go when you’re ready.’"

#. VAR: bhaddaṃ yānaṃ → bhadraṃ yānaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:98.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā "
"bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Prince Vipassī mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine "
"carriages, set out for the park."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="91"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.22"></a>
#. VAR: bhoggaṃ → bhaggaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:99.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto purisaṃ jiṇṇaṃ "
"gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ daṇḍaparāyanaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantaṃ āturaṃ "
"gatayobbanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Along the way he saw an elderly man, bent double, crooked, leaning on a "
"staff, trembling as he walked, ailing, past his prime."

msgctxt "dn14:99.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:99.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pana, samma sārathi, puriso kiṃkato?"
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, what has that man done?"

msgctxt "dn14:99.4"
msgid "Kesāpissa na yathā aññesaṃ, kāyopissa na yathā aññesan’ti."
msgstr "For his hair and his body are unlike those of other men.’"

msgctxt "dn14:99.5"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, jiṇṇo nāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘That, sire, is called an old man.’"

msgctxt "dn14:99.6"
msgid "‘Kiṃ paneso, samma sārathi, jiṇṇo nāmā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why is he called an old man?’"

msgctxt "dn14:99.7"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, jiṇṇo nāma."
msgstr "‘He’s called an old man because now he has not long to live.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:99.8"
msgid "Na dāni tena ciraṃ jīvitabbaṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:99.9"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, ahampi jarādhammo, jaraṃ anatīto’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘But my dear charioteer, am I liable to grow old? Am I not exempt from old "
"age?’"

msgctxt "dn14:99.10"
msgid "‘Tvañca, deva, mayañcamha sabbe jarādhammā, jaraṃ anatītā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Everyone is liable to grow old, sire, including you. No-one is exempt from "
"old age.’"

msgctxt "dn14:99.11"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma sārathi, alaṃ dānajja uyyānabhūmiyā."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, my dear charioteer, that’s enough of the park for today. Let’s "
"return to the royal compound.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:99.12"
msgid "Itova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāhī’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:99.13"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā "
"tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsi."
msgstr "‘Yes, sire,’ replied the charioteer and did so."

msgctxt "dn14:99.14"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro antepuraṃ gato dukkhī dummano "
"pajjhāyati:"
msgstr ""
"Back at the royal compound, the prince, miserable and sad, was brooding:"

msgctxt "dn14:99.15"
msgid ""
"‘dhiratthu kira, bho, jāti nāma, yatra hi nāma jātassa jarā paññāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Damn this thing called birth, since old age will come to anyone who’s born.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="92"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.3"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:100.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā sārathiṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma summoned the charioteer and said:"

msgctxt "dn14:100.2"
msgid "‘kacci, samma sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha?"
msgstr ""
"‘My dear charioteer, I hope the prince enjoyed himself at the park? I hope "
"he was happy there?’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:100.3"
msgid "Kacci, samma sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti?"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:100.4"
msgid ""
"‘Na kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha, na kho, deva, kumāro "
"uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘No, sire, the prince didn’t enjoy himself at the park.’"

msgctxt "dn14:100.5"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, addasa kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto’ti?"
msgstr "‘But what did he see on the way to the park?’"

msgctxt "dn14:100.6"
msgid ""
"‘Addasā kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto purisaṃ jiṇṇaṃ "
"gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ daṇḍaparāyanaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantaṃ āturaṃ "
"gatayobbanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the charioteer told the king about seeing the old man and the prince’s "
"reaction."

