msgctxt "dn14:110.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito "
"samaṅgībhūto paricāreti."
msgstr "with which the prince amused himself."

msgctxt "dn14:110.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many thousand years had passed, Prince Vipassī had his "
"charioteer drive him to the park once more."

msgctxt "dn14:110.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

# Neither reading vilāta or milāta appears to occur elsewhere in this sense. Comm says "Vilātanti sivikaṃ"; Tika says: "Bhantanettakuppalādi vividhaṃ katvā lātabbato vilāto, vayhaṃ, sivikā cāti āha ‘‘vilātanti sivika’’nti. Sivikāya diṭṭhapubbattā mahāsatto citakapañjaraṃ ‘‘sivika’’nti āha". 
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="101"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.10"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:111.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto mahājanakāyaṃ "
"sannipatitaṃ nānārattānañca dussānaṃ vilātaṃ kayiramānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Along the way he saw a large crowd gathered making a bier out of garments of "
"different colors."

msgctxt "dn14:111.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:111.3"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho so, samma sārathi, mahājanakāyo sannipatito nānārattānañca "
"dussānaṃ vilātaṃ kayiratī’ti?"
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, why is that crowd making a bier?’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.4"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, kālaṅkato nāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘That, sire, is for someone who’s departed.’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.5"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma sārathi, yena so kālaṅkato tena rathaṃ pesehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Well then, drive the chariot up to the departed.’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.6"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā yena "
"so kālaṅkato tena rathaṃ pesesi."
msgstr "‘Yes, sire,’ replied the charioteer, and did so."

msgctxt "dn14:111.7"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro petaṃ kālaṅkataṃ, disvā sārathiṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the prince saw the corpse of the departed, he addressed the charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:111.8"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāyaṃ, samma sārathi, kālaṅkato nāmā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why is he called departed?’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.9"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, kālaṅkato nāma."
msgstr ""
"‘He’s called departed because now his mother and father, his relatives and "
"kin shall see him no more, and he shall never again see them.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:111.10"
msgid ""
"Na dāni taṃ dakkhanti mātā vā pitā vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā, sopi na "
"dakkhissati mātaraṃ vā pitaraṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:111.11"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, ahampi maraṇadhammo maraṇaṃ anatīto;"
msgstr ""
"‘But my dear charioteer, am I liable to die? Am I not exempt from death?"

msgctxt "dn14:111.12"
msgid "mampi na dakkhanti devo vā devī vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā;"
msgstr "Will the king and queen and my other relatives and kin see me no more?"

msgctxt "dn14:111.13"
msgid "ahampi na dakkhissāmi devaṃ vā deviṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite’ti?"
msgstr "And shall I never again see them?’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.14"
msgid "‘Tvañca, deva, mayañcamha sabbe maraṇadhammā maraṇaṃ anatītā;"
msgstr ""
"‘Everyone is liable to die, sire, including you. No-one is exempt from death."

msgctxt "dn14:111.15"
msgid "tampi na dakkhanti devo vā devī vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā;"
msgstr ""
"The king and queen and your other relatives and kin shall see you no more,"

msgctxt "dn14:111.16"
msgid "tvampi na dakkhissasi devaṃ vā deviṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite’ti."
msgstr "and you shall never again see them.’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.17"
msgid ""
"‘Tena hi, samma sārathi, alaṃ dānajja uyyānabhūmiyā, itova antepuraṃ "
"paccaniyyāhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, my dear charioteer, that’s enough of the park for today. Let’s "
"return to the royal compound.’"

msgctxt "dn14:111.18"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā "
"tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsi."
msgstr "‘Yes, sire,’ replied the charioteer and did so."

msgctxt "dn14:111.19"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro antepuraṃ gato dukkhī dummano "
"pajjhāyati:"
msgstr ""
"Back at the royal compound, the prince, miserable and sad, was brooding:"

msgctxt "dn14:111.20"
msgid ""
"‘dhiratthu kira, bho, jāti nāma, yatra hi nāma jātassa jarā paññāyissati, "
"byādhi paññāyissati, maraṇaṃ paññāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Damn this thing called birth, since old age, sickness, and death will come "
"to anyone who’s born.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="102"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.11"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.27"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:112.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā sārathiṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma summoned the charioteer and said:"

msgctxt "dn14:112.2"
msgid ""
"‘kacci, samma sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha, kacci, samma "
"sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘My dear charioteer, I hope the prince enjoyed himself at the park? I hope "
"he was happy there?’"

msgctxt "dn14:112.3"
msgid ""
"‘Na kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha, na kho, deva, kumāro "
"uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘No, sire, the prince didn’t enjoy himself at the park.’"

msgctxt "dn14:112.4"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, addasa kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto’ti?"
msgstr "‘But what did he see on the way to the park?’"

msgctxt "dn14:112.5"
msgid ""
"‘Addasā kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto mahājanakāyaṃ sannipatitaṃ "
"nānārattānañca dussānaṃ vilātaṃ kayiramānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the charioteer told the king about seeing the dead man and the prince’s "
"reaction."

msgctxt "dn14:112.6"
msgid "Disvā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.7"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho so, samma sārathi, mahājanakāyo sannipatito nānārattānañca "
"dussānaṃ vilātaṃ kayiratī”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.8"
msgid "“Eso kho, deva, kālaṅkato nāmā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.9"
msgid "“Tena hi, samma sārathi, yena so kālaṅkato tena rathaṃ pesehī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.10"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho ahaṃ, deva, vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā yena so "
"kālaṅkato tena rathaṃ pesesiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.11"
msgid "Addasā kho, deva, kumāro petaṃ kālaṅkataṃ, disvā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.12"
msgid "“kiṃ panāyaṃ, samma sārathi, kālaṅkato nāmā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.13"
msgid "“Eso kho, deva, kālaṅkato nāma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.14"
msgid ""
"Na dāni taṃ dakkhanti mātā vā pitā vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā, sopi na "
"dakkhissati mātaraṃ vā pitaraṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.15"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, ahampi maraṇadhammo maraṇaṃ anatīto;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.16"
msgid "mampi na dakkhanti devo vā devī vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.17"
msgid "ahampi na dakkhissāmi devaṃ vā deviṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.18"
msgid "“Tvañca, deva, mayañcamha sabbe maraṇadhammā maraṇaṃ anatītā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.19"
msgid ""
"tampi na dakkhanti devo vā devī vā aññe vā ñātisālohitā, tvampi na "
"dakkhissasi devaṃ vā deviṃ vā aññe vā ñātisālohite”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.20"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, samma sārathi, alaṃ dānajja uyyānabhūmiyā, itova antepuraṃ "
"paccaniyyāhī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.21"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho ahaṃ, deva, vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā tatova "
"antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.22"
msgid "So kho, deva, kumāro antepuraṃ gato dukkhī dummano pajjhāyati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:112.23"
msgid ""
"“dhiratthu kira, bho, jāti nāma, yatra hi nāma jātassa jarā paññāyissati, "
"byādhi paññāyissati, maraṇaṃ paññāyissatī”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:113.1"
msgid "8. Pabbajita"
msgstr "The Renunciate"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="103"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.12"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:114.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumassa rañño etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:114.2"
msgid ""
"‘mā heva kho vipassī kumāro na rajjaṃ kāresi, mā heva vipassī kumāro "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji, mā heva nemittānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ assa "
"vacanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Prince Vipassī must not renounce the throne. He must not go forth from the "
"lay life to homelessness. And the words of the brahmin soothsayers must not "
"come true.’"

msgctxt "dn14:114.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa bhiyyoso mattāya "
"pañca kāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpesi:"
msgstr ""
"To prevent this he provided the prince with even more of the five kinds of "
"sensual stimulation,"

msgctxt "dn14:114.4"
msgid ""
"‘yathā vipassī kumāro rajjaṃ kareyya, yathā vipassī kumāro na agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyya, yathā nemittānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ micchā assa vacanan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="104"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:115.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito "
"samaṅgībhūto paricāreti."
msgstr "with which the prince amused himself."

msgctxt "dn14:115.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ "
"bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many thousand years had passed, Prince Vipassī had his "
"charioteer drive him to the park once more."

msgctxt "dn14:115.3"
msgid ""
"‘yojehi, samma sārathi, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma "
"subhūmidassanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:115.4"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā "
"bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojetvā vipassissa kumārassa paṭivedesi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:115.5"
msgid ""
"‘yuttāni kho te, deva, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:115.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā "
"bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyāsi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="105"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.14"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.29"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:116.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto purisaṃ bhaṇḍuṃ "
"pabbajitaṃ kāsāyavasanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Along the way he saw a man, a renunciate with shaven head, wearing an ochre "
"robe."

msgctxt "dn14:116.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:116.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pana, samma sārathi, puriso kiṃkato?"
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, what has that man done?"

msgctxt "dn14:116.4"
msgid "Sīsampissa na yathā aññesaṃ, vatthānipissa na yathā aññesan’ti?"
msgstr "For his head and his clothes are unlike those of other men.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.5"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, pabbajito nāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘That, sire, is called a renunciate.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.6"
msgid "‘Kiṃ paneso, samma sārathi, pabbajito nāmā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why is he called a renunciate?’"

#. VAR: samacariyā → sammacariyā (mr)
#. VAR: kusalakiriyā → kusalacariyā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:116.7"
msgid ""
"‘Eso kho, deva, pabbajito nāma sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu "
"kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘He is called a renunciate because he celebrates principled and fair "
"conduct, wholesome actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for "
"living creatures.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.8"
msgid ""
"‘Sādhu kho so, samma sārathi, pabbajito nāma, sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu "
"samacariyā sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu "
"bhūtānukampā."
msgstr ""
"‘Then I celebrate the one called a renunciate, who celebrates principled and "
"fair conduct, wholesome actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion "
"for living creatures!"

msgctxt "dn14:116.9"
msgid "Tena hi, samma sārathi, yena so pabbajito tena rathaṃ pesehī’ti."
msgstr "Well then, drive the chariot up to that renunciate.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.10"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā yena "
"so pabbajito tena rathaṃ pesesi."
msgstr "‘Yes, sire,’ replied the charioteer, and did so."

msgctxt "dn14:116.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro taṃ pabbajitaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Prince Vipassī said to that renunciate:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:116.12"
msgid ""
"‘tvaṃ pana, samma, kiṃkato, sīsampi te na yathā aññesaṃ, vatthānipi te na "
"yathā aññesan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘My good man, what have you done? For your head and your clothes are unlike "
"those of other men.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.13"
msgid "‘Ahaṃ kho, deva, pabbajito nāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘Sire, I am what is called a renunciate.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.14"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, samma, pabbajito nāmā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why are you called a renunciate?’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.15"
msgid ""
"‘Ahaṃ kho, deva, pabbajito nāma, sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu "
"kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I am called a renunciate because I celebrate principled and fair conduct, "
"wholesome actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for living "
"creatures.’"

msgctxt "dn14:116.16"
msgid ""
"‘Sādhu kho tvaṃ, samma, pabbajito nāma sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā "
"sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Then I celebrate the one called a renunciate, who celebrates principled and "
"fair conduct, wholesome actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion "
"for living creatures!’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:117.1"
msgid "9. Bodhisattapabbajjā"
msgstr "The Going Forth"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="106"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:118.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro sārathiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the prince addressed the charioteer:"

msgctxt "dn14:118.2"
msgid "‘tena hi, samma sārathi, rathaṃ ādāya itova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāhi."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, my dear charioteer, take the chariot and return to the royal "
"compound."

msgctxt "dn14:118.3"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ pana idheva kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I shall shave off my hair and beard right here, dress in ochre robes, and go "
"forth from the lay life into homelessness.’"

msgctxt "dn14:118.4"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā "
"rathaṃ ādāya tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsi."
msgstr "‘Yes, sire,’ replied the charioteer and did so."

msgctxt "dn14:118.5"
msgid ""
"Vipassī pana kumāro tattheva kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni "
"acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji."
msgstr ""
"But Prince Vipassī shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ochre robes, "
"and went forth from the lay life into homelessness."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:119.1"
msgid "10. Mahājanakāyaanupabbajjā"
msgstr "A Great Crowd Goes Forth"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="107"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.16"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:120.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho, bhikkhave, bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā mahājanakāyo "
"caturāsītipāṇasahassāni:"
msgstr "A large crowd of 84,000 people in the capital of Bandhumatī heard"

msgctxt "dn14:120.2"
msgid ""
"‘vipassī kira kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito’ti."
msgstr "that Vipassī had gone forth."

msgctxt "dn14:120.3"
msgid "Sutvāna tesaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "It occurred to them:"

#. VAR: orakā → orikā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:120.4"
msgid ""
"‘na hi nūna so orako dhammavinayo, na sā orakā pabbajjā, yattha vipassī "
"kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajito."
msgstr ""
"‘This must be no ordinary teaching and training, no ordinary going forth in "
"which Prince Vipassī has gone forth."

#. VAR: pana mayan’ti → pana na mayanti (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: kimaṅgaṃ → kimaṅga (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:120.5"
msgid ""
"Vipassīpi nāma kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissati, kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti."
msgstr "If even the prince goes forth, why don’t we do the same?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="108"></a>
#. VAR: mahājanakāyo → mahājanakāyā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:121.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, so bhikkhave, mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni kesamassuṃ "
"ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā vipassiṃ bodhisattaṃ agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajitaṃ anupabbajiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then that great crowd of 84,000 people shaved off their hair and beard, "
"dressed in ochre robes, and followed the one intent on awakening, Vipassī, "
"by going forth from the lay life into homelessness."

# Following PTS in omitting janapada, which seems out of place here, and is absent from the parallel passage in DN 19.
msgctxt "dn14:121.2"
msgid ""
"Tāya sudaṃ, bhikkhave, parisāya parivuto vipassī bodhisatto "
"gāmanigamajanapadarājadhānīsu cārikaṃ carati."
msgstr ""
"Escorted by that assembly, Vipassī wandered on tour among the villages, "
"towns, and capital cities."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="109"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:122.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa "
"evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr "Then as he was in private solitude this thought came to his mind: "

#. VAR: na kho metaṃ → na kho panetaṃ (s1-3, km) | na kho me taṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:122.2"
msgid ""
"‘na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ ākiṇṇo viharāmi, yannūnāhaṃ eko gaṇamhā "
"vūpakaṭṭho vihareyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s not appropriate for me to live in a crowd. Why don’t I live alone, "
"withdrawn from the group?’"

msgctxt "dn14:122.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto aparena samayena eko gaṇamhā "
"vūpakaṭṭho vihāsi, aññeneva tāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni agamaṃsu, "
"aññena maggena vipassī bodhisatto."
msgstr ""
"After some time he withdrew from the group to live alone. The 84,000 went "
"one way, but Vipassī went another."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:123.1"
msgid "11. Bodhisattaabhinivesa"
msgstr "Vipassī’s Reflections"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="110"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.18"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.31"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:124.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa vāsūpagatassa rahogatassa "
"paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Then as Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, was in private solitude this "
"thought came to his mind: "

#. VAR: jīyati ca mīyati ca → jiyyati ca miyyati ca (mr)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:124.2"
msgid ""
"‘kicchaṃ vatāyaṃ loko āpanno, jāyati ca jīyati ca mīyati ca cavati ca "
"upapajjati ca, atha ca panimassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ nappajānāti "
"jarāmaraṇassa, kudāssu nāma imassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ paññāyissati "
"jarāmaraṇassā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Alas, this world has fallen into trouble. It’s born, grows old, dies, "
"passes away, and is reborn, yet it doesn’t understand how to escape from "
"this suffering, from old age and death. Oh, when will an escape be found "
"from this suffering, from old age and death?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="111"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:125.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:125.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there old age and death? What is a condition for old "
"age and death?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:125.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:125.4"
msgid "‘jātiyā kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When birth exists there’s old age and death. Birth is a condition for old "
"age and death.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="112"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:126.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:126.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jāti hoti, kiṃpaccayā jātī’ti?"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there birth? What is a condition for birth?’"

msgctxt "dn14:126.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:126.4"
msgid "‘bhave kho sati jāti hoti, bhavapaccayā jātī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When future existence exists there’s birth. Future existence is a condition "
"for birth.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="113"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:127.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:127.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati bhavo hoti, kiṃpaccayā bhavo’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there future existence? What is a condition for future "
"existence?’"

msgctxt "dn14:127.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:127.4"
msgid "‘upādāne kho sati bhavo hoti, upādānapaccayā bhavo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When grasping exists there’s future existence. Grasping is a condition for "
"future existence.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="114"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:128.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:128.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati upādānaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā upādānan’ti?"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there grasping? What is a condition for grasping?’"

msgctxt "dn14:128.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:128.4"
msgid "‘taṇhāya kho sati upādānaṃ hoti, taṇhāpaccayā upādānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When craving exists there’s grasping. Craving is a condition for grasping.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="115"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:129.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:129.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati taṇhā hoti, kiṃpaccayā taṇhā’ti?"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there craving? What is a condition for craving?’"

msgctxt "dn14:129.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:129.4"
msgid "‘vedanāya kho sati taṇhā hoti, vedanāpaccayā taṇhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When feeling exists there’s craving. Feeling is a condition for craving.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="116"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.32"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:130.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:130.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati vedanā hoti, kiṃpaccayā vedanā’ti?"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there feeling? What is a condition for feeling?’"

msgctxt "dn14:130.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:130.4"
msgid "‘phasse kho sati vedanā hoti, phassapaccayā vedanā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When contact exists there’s feeling. Contact is a condition for feeling.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="117"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:131.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:131.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati phasso hoti, kiṃpaccayā phasso’ti?"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there contact? What is a condition for contact?’"

msgctxt "dn14:131.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:131.4"
msgid "‘saḷāyatane kho sati phasso hoti, saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When the six sense fields exist there’s contact. The six sense fields are a "
"condition for contact.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="118"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:132.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:132.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā saḷāyatanan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists are there the six sense fields? What is a condition for "
"the six sense fields?’"

msgctxt "dn14:132.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:132.4"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti, nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When name and form exist there’s the six sense fields. Name and form are a "
"condition for the six sense fields.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="119"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:133.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:133.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā nāmarūpan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there name and form? What is a condition for name and "
"form?’"

msgctxt "dn14:133.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:133.4"
msgid "‘viññāṇe kho sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When consciousness exists there’s name and form. Consciousness is a "
"condition for name and form.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="120"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:134.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought: "

msgctxt "dn14:134.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā viññāṇan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there consciousness? What is a condition for "
"consciousness?’"

msgctxt "dn14:134.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:134.4"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When name and form exist there’s consciousness. Name and form are a "
"condition for consciousness.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="121"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.19"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.33"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:135.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:135.2"
msgid "‘paccudāvattati kho idaṃ viññāṇaṃ nāmarūpamhā, nāparaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"‘This consciousness turns back from name and form, and doesn’t go beyond "
"that.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:135.3"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā jāyetha vā jiyyetha vā miyyetha vā cavetha vā upapajjetha vā, "
"yadidaṃ nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ, nāmarūpapaccayā "
"saḷāyatanaṃ, saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, vedanāpaccayā "
"taṇhā, taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ, upādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, "
"jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"It is to this extent that one may be reborn, grow old, die, pass away, or "
"reappear. That is: name and form is a condition for consciousness. "
"Consciousness is a condition for name and form. Name and form is a condition "
"for the six sense fields. The six sense fields are conditions for contact. "
"Contact is a condition for feeling. Feeling is a condition for craving. "
"Craving is a condition for grasping. Grasping is a condition for future "
"existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a "
"condition for old age and death, sorrow, crying, pain, sadness, and distress "
"to come to be."

msgctxt "dn14:135.4"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti’."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="122"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:136.1"
msgid ""
"‘Samudayo samudayo’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa pubbe "
"ananussutesu dhammesu cakkhuṃ udapādi, ñāṇaṃ udapādi, paññā udapādi, vijjā "
"udapādi, āloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"‘Origination, origination.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, "
"realization, and light that arose in Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, "
"regarding teachings not learned before from another."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="123"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:137.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:137.2"
msgid ""
"‘kimhi nu kho asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what doesn’t exist is there no old age and death? When what ceases do "
"old age and death cease?’"

msgctxt "dn14:137.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:137.4"
msgid ""
"‘jātiyā kho asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When birth doesn’t exist there’s no old age and death. When birth ceases, "
"old age and death cease.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="124"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:138.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:138.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati jāti na hoti, kissa nirodhā jātinirodho’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what doesn’t exist is there no birth? When what ceases does birth "
"cease?’"

msgctxt "dn14:138.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya "
"abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through rational focus, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "dn14:138.4"
msgid "‘bhave kho asati jāti na hoti, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When future existence doesn’t exist there’s no birth. When future existence "
"ceases, birth ceases.’"

