msgid ""
"‘nāmarūpe kho asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti, nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When name and form don’t exist there’s no consciousness. When name and form "
"cease, consciousness ceases.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="133"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.21"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.35"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:147.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought:"

# The PTS's inclusion of vipassana here, unaccountably followed by RD and MW, is an egregious and embarassing error. No manuscript contains this reading, and the PTS edition itself states that the word is found only in the commentary. To be clear, there it is obviously presented not as a reading but as an explanation: "Maggoti vipassanāmaggo."
msgctxt "dn14:147.2"
msgid "‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ maggo sambodhāya yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘I have discovered the path to awakening. That is:"

msgctxt "dn14:147.3"
msgid ""
"nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho, viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho, "
"nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho, saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho, "
"phassanirodhā vedanānirodho, vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho, taṇhānirodhā "
"upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, "
"jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"When name and form cease, consciousness ceases. When consciousness ceases, "
"name and form cease. When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease. "
"When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. When contact ceases, "
"feeling ceases. When feeling ceases, craving ceases. When craving ceases, "
"grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, future existence ceases. When future "
"existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, "
"sorrow, crying, pain, sadness, and distress cease."

msgctxt "dn14:147.4"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti’."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="134"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:148.1"
msgid ""
"‘Nirodho nirodho’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa pubbe "
"ananussutesu dhammesu cakkhuṃ udapādi, ñāṇaṃ udapādi, paññā udapādi, vijjā "
"udapādi, āloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"‘Cessation, cessation.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, realization, "
"and light that arose in Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, regarding "
"teachings not learned before from another."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="135"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:149.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto aparena samayena pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī vihāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Some time later Vipassī meditated observing rise and fall in the five sets "
"of phenomena connected with grasping."

msgctxt "dn14:149.2"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"‘Such are physical phenomena, such is the origin of physical phenomena, such "
"is the ending of physical phenomena."

msgctxt "dn14:149.3"
msgid "iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of "
"feeling."

msgctxt "dn14:149.4"
msgid "iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of "
"perception."

msgctxt "dn14:149.5"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of "
"choices."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:149.6"
msgid ""
"iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti, tassa "
"pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassino viharato na cirasseva "
"anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccīti."
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness.’ Meditating like this his mind was soon freed from "
"defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn14:150.1"
msgid "Dutiyabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:151.1"
msgid "12. Brahmayācanakathā"
msgstr "12 The Appeal of Brahmā"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="136"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.36"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:152.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, "
"thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:152.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I teach the Dhamma?’"

msgctxt "dn14:152.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:152.4"
msgid ""
"‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto "
"atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo."
msgstr ""
"‘This principle I have discovered is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, "
"peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the "
"astute."

msgctxt "dn14:152.5"
msgid "Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā."
msgstr "But people like attachment, they love it and enjoy it."

msgctxt "dn14:152.6"
msgid ""
"Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ "
"ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo."
msgstr ""
"It’s hard for them to see this thing; that is, specific conditionality, "
"dependent origination."

msgctxt "dn14:152.7"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s also hard for them to see this thing; that is, the stilling of all "
"activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading "
"away, cessation, extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn14:152.8"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"And if I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which "
"would be wearying and troublesome for me.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:152.9"
msgid "so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā’ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="137"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:153.1"
msgid ""
"Apissu, bhikkhave, vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ imā "
"anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā:"
msgstr ""
"And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor "
"learned before in the past, occurred to him:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="138"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:154.1"
msgid "‘Kicchena me adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "‘I’ve struggled hard to realize this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:154.2"
msgid "halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ;"
msgstr "enough with trying to explain it!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:154.3"
msgid "Rāgadosaparetehi,"
msgstr "This teaching is not easily understood"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:154.4"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho."
msgstr "by those mired in greed and hate."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="139"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:155.1"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ,"
msgstr "Those caught up in greed can’t see"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:155.2"
msgid "gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ;"
msgstr "what’s subtle, going against the stream, "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:155.3"
msgid "Rāgarattā na dakkhanti,"
msgstr "deep, hard to see, and very fine,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:155.4"
msgid "tamokhandhena āvuṭā’ti."
msgstr "for they’re shrouded in a mass of darkness.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="140"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:156.1"
msgid ""
"Itiha, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ nami, no dhammadesanāya."
msgstr ""
"So, as the Buddha Vipassī reflected like this, his mind inclined to "
"remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="141"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.37"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:157.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññatarassa mahābrahmuno vipassissa bhagavato arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"Then a certain Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, "
"thought:"

#. VAR: namati → nami (s1-3, km, mr) | namissati (?)
msgctxt "dn14:157.2"
msgid ""
"‘nassati vata bho loko, vinassati vata bho loko, yatra hi nāma vipassissa "
"bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati, no "
"dhammadesanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh my goodness! The world will be lost, the world will perish! For the mind "
"of the Realized One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, "
"inclines to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’"

msgctxt "dn14:157.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ "
"vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm,"

msgctxt "dn14:157.4"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:157.5"
msgid ""
"brahmaloke antarahito vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa purato "
"pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha "
"Vipassī."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.3"></a>
#. VAR: nihantvā → nidahanto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:157.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dakkhiṇaṃ "
"jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ pathaviyaṃ nihantvā yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his "
"cupped palms toward the Buddha Vipassī, and said:"

#. VAR: santi → santīdha (s1-3, km)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:157.7"
msgid ""
"‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ, santi sattā "
"apparajakkhajātikā;"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! Let the Holy One teach the "
"Dhamma!"

msgctxt "dn14:157.8"
msgid "assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti."
msgstr ""
"There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because "
"they haven’t heard the teaching. There will be those who understand the "
"teaching!’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="142"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.4"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.38"></a>
#. VAR: Evaṃ vutte → atha kho (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn14:158.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho taṃ "
"mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the Buddha Vipassī said to him:"

msgctxt "dn14:158.2"
msgid "‘mayhampi kho, brahme, etadahosi:"
msgstr "‘I too thought this, Brahmā:"

msgctxt "dn14:158.3"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Why don’t I teach the Dhamma?”"

msgctxt "dn14:158.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, brahme, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "dn14:158.5"
msgid ""
"“adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto "
"atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:158.6"
msgid "Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:158.7"
msgid ""
"Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ "
"ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:158.8"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:158.9"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“If I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would "
"be wearying and troublesome for me."

msgctxt "dn14:158.10"
msgid "so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:158.11"
msgid ""
"Apissu maṃ, brahme, imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="143"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:159.1"
msgid "“Kicchena me adhigataṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:159.2"
msgid "halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:159.3"
msgid "Rāgadosaparetehi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:159.4"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="144"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:160.1"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:160.2"
msgid "gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:160.3"
msgid "Rāgarattā na dakkhanti,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:160.4"
msgid "tamokhandhena āvuṭā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="145"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:161.1"
msgid ""
"Itiha me, brahme, paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ nami, no "
"dhammadesanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"So, as I reflected like this, my mind inclined to remaining passive, not to "
"teaching the Dhamma.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="146"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:162.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā …"
msgstr "For a second time,"

msgctxt "dn14:162.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:162.3"
msgid ""
"tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ "
"sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and a third time that Great Brahmā begged the Buddha to teach."

msgctxt "dn14:162.4"
msgid ""
"‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ, santi sattā "
"apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, bhavissanti dhammassa "
"aññātāro’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="147"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.6"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.39"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:163.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brahmuno ca "
"ajjhesanaṃ viditvā sattesu ca kāruññataṃ paṭicca buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ "
"volokesi."
msgstr ""
"Then, understanding Brahmā’s invitation, the Buddha Vipassī surveyed the "
"world with the eye of a Buddha, because of his compassion for sentient "
"beings."

#. VAR: suviññāpaye duviññāpaye → duviññāpaye bhabbe abhabbe (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:163.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho buddhacakkhunā "
"lokaṃ volokento satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye "
"svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce "
"paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na "
"paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante."
msgstr ""
"And he saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with "
"much dust in their eyes; with keen faculties and with weak faculties, with "
"good qualities and with bad qualities, easy to teach and hard to teach. And "
"some of them lived seeing the danger in the flaw to do with the next world, "
"while others did not."

msgctxt "dn14:163.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni "
"uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni "
"udakānuggatāni anto nimuggaposīni."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of "
"them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving "
"underwater. Some of them sprout and grow in the water reaching the water’s "
"surface. And some of them sprout and grow in the water but rise up above the "
"water and stand with no water clinging to them."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:163.4"
msgid ""
"Appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake "
"saṃvaḍḍhāni samodakaṃ ṭhitāni."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:163.5"
msgid ""
"Appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake "
"saṃvaḍḍhāni udakā accuggamma ṭhitāni anupalittāni udakena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:163.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho buddhacakkhunā "
"lokaṃ volokento addasa satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye "
"mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce "
"paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na "
"paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the Buddha Vipassī saw sentient beings with little dust in "
"their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="148"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:164.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā vipassissa bhagavato arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ "
"arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then that Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, "
"addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="149"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:165.1"
msgid "‘Sele yathā pabbatamuddhaniṭṭhito,"
msgstr "‘Standing high on a rocky mountain,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:165.2"
msgid "Yathāpi passe janataṃ samantato;"
msgstr "you can see the people all around."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:165.3"
msgid "Tathūpamaṃ dhammamayaṃ sumedha,"
msgstr "In just the same way, all-seer, wise one,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:165.4"
msgid "Pāsādamāruyha samantacakkhu;"
msgstr "ascend the palace built of Dhamma!"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ → sokāvakiṇṇaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:165.5"
msgid "Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ janatamapetasoko,"
msgstr "You’re free of sorrow; but look at these people"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:165.6"
msgid "Avekkhassu jātijarābhibhūtaṃ."
msgstr "overwhelmed with sorrow, oppressed by rebirth and old age."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="150"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:166.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi vīra vijitasaṅgāma,"
msgstr "Rise, hero! Victor in battle, leader of the caravan,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:166.2"
msgid "Satthavāha aṇaṇa vicara loke;"
msgstr "wander the world without obligation."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Desassu → desetu (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:166.3"
msgid "Desassu bhagavā dhammaṃ,"
msgstr "Let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:166.4"
msgid "Aññātāro bhavissantī’ti."
msgstr "There will be those who understand!’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="151"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:167.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha Vipassī addressed that Great Brahmā in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="152"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:168.1"
msgid "‘Apārutā tesaṃ amatassa dvārā,"
msgstr "‘Flung open are the doors to the deathless!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:168.2"
msgid "Ye sotavanto pamuñcantu saddhaṃ;"
msgstr "Let those with ears to hear decide their faith."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:168.3"
msgid "Vihiṃsasaññī paguṇaṃ na bhāsiṃ,"
msgstr "Thinking it would be troublesome, Brahmā, I did not teach"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:168.4"
msgid "Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ manujesu brahme’ti."
msgstr "the sophisticated, sublime Dhamma among humans.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="153"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.40"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:169.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā:"
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing that his request for the Buddha Vipassī to "
"teach the Dhamma had been granted, bowed and respectfully circled me, "
"keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:169.2"
msgid ""
"‘katāvakāso khomhi vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"dhammadesanāyā’ti vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi."
msgstr " "

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:170.1"
msgid "13. Aggasāvakayuga"
msgstr "The Chief Disciples"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="154"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:171.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, "
"thought:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:171.2"
msgid ""
"‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva "
"ājānissatī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Who should I teach first of all? Who will quickly understand this teaching?’"

msgctxt "dn14:171.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "dn14:171.4"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto bandhumatiyā "
"rājadhāniyā paṭivasanti paṇḍitā viyattā medhāvino dīgharattaṃ "
"apparajakkhajātikā."
msgstr ""
"‘That Khaṇḍa, the king’s son, and Tissa, the high priest’s son, are astute, "
"competent, clever, and have long had little dust in his eyes."

msgctxt "dn14:171.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ khaṇḍassa ca rājaputtassa, tissassa ca purohitaputtassa paṭhamaṃ "
"dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, te imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I teach them first of all? They will quickly understand this "
"teaching.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="155"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:172.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho seyyathāpi nāma "
"balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm,"

msgctxt "dn14:172.2"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

# Comm takes khema as a proper name; it is a common name for sanctuaries in the Jatakas.
msgctxt "dn14:172.3"
msgid ""
"bodhirukkhamūle antarahito bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā kheme migadāye "
"pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"he vanished from the tree of awakening and reappeared near the capital city "
"of Bandhumatī, in the deer park named Sanctuary."

#. VAR: dāyapālaṃ → migadāyapālaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:172.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dāyapālaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha Vipassī addressed the park keeper:"

msgctxt "dn14:172.5"
msgid ""
"‘ehi tvaṃ, samma dāyapāla, bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ pavisitvā khaṇḍañca "
"rājaputtaṃ tissañca purohitaputtaṃ evaṃ vadehi—"
msgstr ""
"‘My dear park keeper, please enter the city and say this to the king’s son "
"Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa:"

msgctxt "dn14:172.6"
msgid ""
"vipassī, bhante, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ "
"anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati, so tumhākaṃ dassanakāmo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened "
"Buddha, has arrived at Bandhumatī and is staying in the deer park named "
"Sanctuary. He wishes to see you.’"

msgctxt "dn14:172.7"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhante’ti kho, bhikkhave, dāyapālo vipassissa bhagavato arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa paṭissutvā bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ pavisitvā khaṇḍañca "
"rājaputtaṃ tissañca purohitaputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "‘Yes, sir,’ replied the park keeper, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn14:172.8"
msgid ""
"‘vipassī, bhante, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ "
"anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati;"
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:172.9"
msgid "so tumhākaṃ dassanakāmo’ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="156"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.10"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.41"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:173.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto bhaddāni "
"bhaddāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi "
"bhaddehi yānehi bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā niyyiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa had the finest "
"carriages harnessed. Then they mounted a fine carriage and, along with other "
"fine carriages, set out from Bandhumatī for the Sanctuary."

msgctxt "dn14:173.2"
msgid "Yena khemo migadāyo tena pāyiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: pattikāva → pattikā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:173.3"
msgid ""
"Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikāva yena "
"vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and "
"approached the Buddha Vipassī on foot. "

msgctxt "dn14:173.4"
msgid ""
"Upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "They bowed and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="157"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.11"></a>
#. VAR: anupubbiṃ kathaṃ → anupubbīkathaṃ (s1-3, km) | ānupubbikathaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:174.1"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The Buddha Vipassī taught them step by step, with"

msgctxt "dn14:174.2"
msgid ""
"dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ "
"nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""
"talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of "
"sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation."

msgctxt "dn14:174.3"
msgid ""
"Yadā te bhagavā aññāsi kallacitte muducitte vinīvaraṇacitte udaggacitte "
"pasannacitte, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr ""
"And when he knew that their minds were ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, "
"joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "dn14:174.4"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ."
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "dn14:174.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇheyya;"
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "dn14:174.6"
msgid ""
"evameva khaṇḍassa ca rājaputtassa tissassa ca purohitaputtassa tasmiṃyeva "
"āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"in that very seat the spotless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in the "
"king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa:"

msgctxt "dn14:174.7"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti."
msgstr "‘Everything that has a beginning has an end.’ "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="158"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.12"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.42"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:175.1"
msgid ""
"Te diṭṭhadhammā pattadhammā viditadhammā pariyogāḷhadhammā tiṇṇavicikicchā "
"vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane vipassiṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"They saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. They went beyond "
"doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of "
"others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. They said to the Buddha Vipassī:"

msgctxt "dn14:175.2"
msgid "‘abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "‘Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn14:175.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark "

msgctxt "dn14:175.4"
msgid "“cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī”ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there, "

msgctxt "dn14:175.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn14:175.6"
msgid "Ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to the Blessed One, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn14:175.7"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyāma "
"upasampadan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may we receive the going forth and ordination in the Buddha’s presence?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="159"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:176.1"
msgid ""
"Alatthuṃ kho, bhikkhave, khaṇḍo ca rājaputto, tisso ca purohitaputto "
"vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ alatthuṃ "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And they received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha Vipassī’s "
"presence."

msgctxt "dn14:176.2"
msgid ""
"Te vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha Vipassī educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them "
"with a Dharma talk."

#. VAR: nibbāne → nibbāne va (bj) | nekkhamme (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:176.3"
msgid "saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ nibbāne ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""
"He explained the drawbacks of conditioned phenomena, so sordid and corrupt, "
"and the benefit of extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn14:176.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassiyamānānaṃ samādapiyamānānaṃ samuttejiyamānānaṃ sampahaṃsiyamānānaṃ "
"nacirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Being taught like this their minds were soon freed from defilements by not "
"grasping."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:177.1"
msgid "14. Mahājanakāyapabbajjā"
msgstr "The Going Forth of the Large Crowd"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="160"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.14"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.43"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:178.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho, bhikkhave, bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā mahājanakāyo "
"caturāsītipāṇasahassāni:"
msgstr "A large crowd of 84,000 people in the capital of Bandhumatī heard"

msgctxt "dn14:178.2"
msgid ""
"‘vipassī kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto "
"kheme migadāye viharati."
msgstr ""
"that the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, "
"had arrived at Bandhumatī and was staying in the deer park named Sanctuary. "

msgctxt "dn14:178.3"
msgid ""
"Khaṇḍo ca kira rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto vipassissa bhagavato arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa santike kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And they heard that the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa "
"had shaved off their hair and beard, dressed in ochre robes, and gone forth "
"from the lay life into homelessness in the Buddha’s presence."

msgctxt "dn14:178.4"
msgid "Sutvāna nesaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "It occurred to them:"

msgctxt "dn14:178.5"
msgid ""
"‘na hi nūna so orako dhammavinayo, na sā orakā pabbajjā, yattha khaṇḍo ca "
"rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni "
"acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā."
msgstr ""
"‘This must be no ordinary teaching and training, no ordinary going forth in "
"which the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa have gone forth."

msgctxt "dn14:178.6"
msgid ""
"Khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni "
"vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissanti, kimaṅgaṃ pana "
"mayan’ti."
msgstr "If even they go forth, why don’t we do the same?’"

msgctxt "dn14:178.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni bandhumatiyā "
"rājadhāniyā nikkhamitvā yena khemo migadāyo yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then those 84,000 people left Bandhumatī for the Sanctuary, where they "
"approached the Buddha Vipassī,"

msgctxt "dn14:178.8"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="161"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:179.1"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi."
msgstr "The Buddha Vipassī taught them step by step, with"

msgctxt "dn14:179.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:179.3"
msgid ""
"dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ "
"nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""
"talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of "
"sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation."

msgctxt "dn14:179.4"
msgid ""
"Yadā te bhagavā aññāsi kallacitte muducitte vinīvaraṇacitte udaggacitte "
"pasannacitte, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr ""
"And when he knew that their minds were ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, "
"joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "dn14:179.5"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ."
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "dn14:179.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇheyya;"
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "dn14:179.7"
msgid ""
"evameva tesaṃ caturāsītipāṇasahassānaṃ tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ "
"dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"in that very seat the spotless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in "
"those 84,000 people: "

msgctxt "dn14:179.8"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti."
msgstr "‘Everything that has a beginning has an end.’ "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="162"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:180.1"
msgid ""
"Te diṭṭhadhammā pattadhammā viditadhammā pariyogāḷhadhammā tiṇṇavicikicchā "
"vigatakathaṃkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane vipassiṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"They saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. They went beyond "
"doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of "
"others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. They said to the Buddha Vipassī:"

msgctxt "dn14:180.2"
msgid "‘abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "‘Excellent, sir! Excellent!’"

msgctxt "dn14:180.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"And just like Khaṇḍa and Tissa they asked for and received ordination. Then "
"the Buddha taught them further."

msgctxt "dn14:180.4"
msgid "“cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī”ti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:180.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:180.6"
msgid ""
"Ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:180.7"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ labheyyāma "
"upasampadan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="163"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.17"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.44"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:181.1"
msgid ""
"Alatthuṃ kho, bhikkhave, tāni caturāsītipāṇasahassāni vipassissa bhagavato "
"arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alatthuṃ upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:181.2"
msgid ""
"Te vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:181.3"
msgid "saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ nibbāne ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:181.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassiyamānānaṃ samādapiyamānānaṃ samuttejiyamānānaṃ sampahaṃsiyamānānaṃ "
"nacirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Being taught like this their minds were soon freed from defilements by not "
"grasping."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:182.1"
msgid "15. Purimapabbajitānaṃ dhammābhisamaya"
msgstr "The 84,000 Who Had Gone Forth Previously"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="164"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:183.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho, bhikkhave, tāni purimāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni:"
msgstr "The 84,000 people who had gone forth previously also heard:"

msgctxt "dn14:183.2"
msgid ""
"‘vipassī kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto "
"kheme migadāye viharati, dhammañca kira desetī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It seems the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened "
"Buddha, has arrived at Bandhumatī and was staying in the deer park named "
"Sanctuary. And he is teaching the Dhamma!’"

msgctxt "dn14:183.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, tāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni yena bandhumatī "
"rājadhānī yena khemo migadāyo yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then they too went to see the Buddha Vipassī, realized the Dhamma, went "
"forth, and became freed from defilements."

msgctxt "dn14:183.4"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="165"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:184.1"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.3"
msgid ""
"dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ "
"nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.4"
msgid ""
"Yadā te bhagavā aññāsi kallacitte muducitte vinīvaraṇacitte udaggacitte "
"pasannacitte, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.5"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇheyya;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.7"
msgid ""
"evameva tesaṃ caturāsītipabbajitasahassānaṃ tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ "
"vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:184.8"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="166"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.20"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.45"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:185.1"
msgid ""
"Te diṭṭhadhammā pattadhammā viditadhammā pariyogāḷhadhammā tiṇṇavicikicchā "
"vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane vipassiṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.2"
msgid "‘abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.4"
msgid "“cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī”ti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.6"
msgid ""
"Ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:185.7"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ labheyyāma "
"upasampadan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="167"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:186.1"
msgid ""
"Alatthuṃ kho, bhikkhave, tāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni vipassissa "
"bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ alatthuṃ upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:186.2"
msgid ""
"Te vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:186.3"
msgid "saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ nibbāne ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:186.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassiyamānānaṃ samādapiyamānānaṃ samuttejiyamānānaṃ sampahaṃsiyamānānaṃ "
"nacirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:187.1"
msgid "16. Cārikāanujānana"
msgstr "16 The Allowance to Wander"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="168"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.22"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.46"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:188.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā "
"mahābhikkhusaṅgho paṭivasati aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a large Saṅgha of 6,800,000 mendicants were residing at "
"Bandhumatī."

msgctxt "dn14:188.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa "
"rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"As the Buddha Vipassī was in private solitude this thought came to his mind:"

msgctxt "dn14:188.3"
msgid ""
"‘mahā kho etarahi bhikkhusaṅgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati "
"aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, yannūnāhaṃ bhikkhū anujāneyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha residing at Bandhumatī now is large. What if I was to urge them:"

msgctxt "dn14:188.4"
msgid ""
"“caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Wander forth, mendicants, for the welfare and happiness of many people, out "
"of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods "
"and humans. "

msgctxt "dn14:188.5"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha;"
msgstr "Let not two go by one road."

msgctxt "dn14:188.6"
msgid ""
"desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ "
"sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha."
msgstr ""
"Teach the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And explain a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:188.7"
msgid ""
"Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
"bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro."
msgstr ""
"There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because "
"they haven’t heard the teaching. There will be those who understand the "
"teaching!"

msgctxt "dn14:188.8"
msgid ""
"Api ca channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī "
"upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā”’ti."
msgstr ""
"But when six years have passed, you must all come to Bandhumatī to recite "
"the code of conduct.”’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="169"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.23"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.47"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:189.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro mahābrahmā vipassissa bhagavato arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya seyyathāpi nāma balavā "
"puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr ""
"Then a certain Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, "
"as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm,"

msgctxt "dn14:189.2"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:189.3"
msgid ""
"brahmaloke antarahito vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa purato "
"pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha Vipassī."

msgctxt "dn14:189.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena vipassī "
"bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ "
"arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his "
"cupped palms toward the Buddha Vipassī, and said:"

msgctxt "dn14:189.5"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata."
msgstr "‘That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!"

msgctxt "dn14:189.6"
msgid ""
"Mahā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhusaṃgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati "
"aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, anujānātu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhū:"
msgstr ""
"The Saṅgha residing at Bandhumatī now is large. Please urge them to wander, "
"as you thought."

msgctxt "dn14:189.7"
msgid ""
"“caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:189.8"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:189.9"
msgid ""
"desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ "
"sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: aññātāro”ti → aññātāro (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:189.10"
msgid ""
"Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
"bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:189.11"
msgid ""
"Api ca, bhante, mayaṃ tathā karissāma yathā bhikkhū channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ "
"accayena bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamissanti pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And sir, I’ll make sure that when six years have passed the mendicants will "
"return to Bandhumatī to recite the code of conduct.’"

msgctxt "dn14:189.12"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā."
msgstr "That’s what that Great Brahmā said."

msgctxt "dn14:189.13"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ vatvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi."
msgstr ""
"Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha Vipassī, keeping him on "
"his right side, before vanishing right there."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="170"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:190.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sāyanhasamayaṃ "
"paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha Vipassī came out of solitude and "
"addressed the mendicants, telling them all that had happened. Then he said:"

msgctxt "dn14:190.2"
msgid ""
"‘idha mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.3"
msgid ""
"“mahā kho etarahi bhikkhusaṅgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati "
"aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ bhikkhū anujāneyyaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.5"
msgid ""
"caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.6"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.7"
msgid ""
"desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ "
"sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.8"
msgid ""
"Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
"bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:190.9"
msgid ""
"Api ca channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī "
"upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="171"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.25"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.48"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:191.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro mahābrahmā mama cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya "
"seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.2"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.3"
msgid "brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yenāhaṃ "
"tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.5"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.6"
msgid ""
"Mahā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhusaṅgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati "
"aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.7"
msgid "Anujānātu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhū—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.8"
msgid ""
"caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.9"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.10"
msgid "desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.12"
msgid ""
"santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
"bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāroti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.13"
msgid ""
"Api ca, bhante, mayaṃ tathā karissāma, yathā bhikkhū channaṃ channaṃ "
"vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamissanti "
"pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.14"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:191.15"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="172"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:192.1"
msgid ""
"‘Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caratha cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya "
"lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘Wander forth, mendicants, for the welfare and happiness of many people, out "
"of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods "
"and humans. "

msgctxt "dn14:192.2"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha;"
msgstr "Let not two go by one road."

msgctxt "dn14:192.3"
msgid ""
"desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ "
"sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha."
msgstr ""
"Teach the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And explain a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

msgctxt "dn14:192.4"
msgid ""
"Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
"bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro."
msgstr ""
"There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because "
"they haven’t heard the teaching. There will be those who understand the "
"teaching!"

msgctxt "dn14:192.5"
msgid ""
"Api ca, bhikkhave, channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī "
"upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"But when six years have passed, you must all come to Bandhumatī to recite "
"the code of conduct.’"

msgctxt "dn14:192.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yebhuyyena ekāheneva janapadacārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then most of the mendicants departed to wander the country that very day."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="173"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.27"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.49"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:193.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena jambudīpe caturāsīti āvāsasahassāni honti."
msgstr "Now at that time there were 84,000 monasteries in India."

msgctxt "dn14:193.2"
msgid "Ekamhi hi vasse nikkhante devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ:"
msgstr "And when the first year came to an end the deities raised the cry:"

msgctxt "dn14:193.3"
msgid "‘nikkhantaṃ kho, mārisā, ekaṃ vassaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Good sirs, the first year has ended."

msgctxt "dn14:193.4"
msgid "pañca dāni vassāni sesāni;"
msgstr "Now five years remain."

msgctxt "dn14:193.5"
msgid ""
"pañcannaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā "
"pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"When five years have passed, you must all go to Bandhumatī to recite the "
"code of conduct.’"

msgctxt "dn14:193.6"
msgid "Dvīsu vassesu nikkhantesu …"
msgstr "And when the second year … "

msgctxt "dn14:193.7"
msgid "tīsu vassesu nikkhantesu …"
msgstr "the third year …"

msgctxt "dn14:193.8"
msgid "catūsu vassesu nikkhantesu …"
msgstr "the fourth year …"

msgctxt "dn14:193.9"
msgid "pañcasu vassesu nikkhantesu devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ:"
msgstr "the fifth year came to an end, the deities raised the cry:"

msgctxt "dn14:193.10"
msgid "‘nikkhantāni kho, mārisā, pañcavassāni;"
msgstr "‘Good sirs, the fifth year has ended."

msgctxt "dn14:193.11"
msgid "ekaṃ dāni vassaṃ sesaṃ;"
msgstr "Now one year remains."

msgctxt "dn14:193.12"
msgid ""
"ekassa vassassa accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā "
"pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"When one year has passed, you must all go to Bandhumatī to recite the code "
"of conduct.’"

msgctxt "dn14:193.13"
msgid "Chasu vassesu nikkhantesu devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ:"
msgstr "And when the sixth year came to an end the deities raised the cry:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:193.14"
msgid ""
"‘nikkhantāni kho, mārisā, chabbassāni, samayo dāni bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ "
"upasaṅkamituṃ pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sirs, the sixth year has ended. Now is the time that you must go to "
"Bandhumatī to recite the code of conduct.’"

msgctxt "dn14:193.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū appekacce sakena iddhānubhāvena appekacce "
"devatānaṃ iddhānubhāvena ekāheneva bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamiṃsu "
"pātimokkhuddesāyāti."
msgstr ""
"Then that very day the mendicants went to Bandhumatī to recite the code of "
"conduct. Some went by their own psychic powers, and some by the psychic "
"powers of the deities."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="174"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:194.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhikkhusaṅghe "
"evaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisati:"
msgstr ""
"And there the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened "
"Buddha, recited the code of conduct thus:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="175"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:195.1"
msgid "‘Khantī paramaṃ tapo titikkhā,"
msgstr "‘Patient acceptance is the highest austerity."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:195.2"
msgid "Nibbānaṃ paramaṃ vadanti buddhā;"
msgstr "Extinguishment is the highest, say the Buddhas."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:195.3"
msgid "Na hi pabbajito parūpaghātī,"
msgstr "No true renunciate injures another,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:195.4"
msgid "Na samaṇo hoti paraṃ viheṭhayanto."
msgstr "nor does an ascetic hurt another."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="176"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:196.1"
msgid "Sabbapāpassa akaraṇaṃ,"
msgstr "Not to do any evil;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:196.2"
msgid "kusalassa upasampadā;"
msgstr "to undertake the good;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:196.3"
msgid "Sacittapariyodapanaṃ,"
msgstr "to purify one’s mind:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:196.4"
msgid "etaṃ buddhānasāsanaṃ."
msgstr "this is the instruction of the Buddhas."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="177"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.50"></a>
#. VAR: Anūpavādo anūpaghāto → anupavādo anupaghāto (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn14:197.1"
msgid "Anūpavādo anūpaghāto,"
msgstr "Not speaking ill nor doing harm;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:197.2"
msgid "Pātimokkhe ca saṃvaro;"
msgstr "restraint in the code of conduct;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:197.3"
msgid "Mattaññutā ca bhattasmiṃ,"
msgstr "moderation in eating;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:197.4"
msgid "Pantañca sayanāsanaṃ;"
msgstr "staying in remote lodgings;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:197.5"
msgid "Adhicitte ca āyogo,"
msgstr "commitment to the higher mind—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn14:197.6"
msgid "Etaṃ buddhānasāsanan’ti."
msgstr "This is the instruction of the Buddhas.’"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:198.1"
msgid "17. Devatārocana"
msgstr "17 Being Informed by Deities"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="178"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.29"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.51"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:199.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamidāhaṃ, bhikkhave, samayaṃ ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ viharāmi subhagavane sālarājamūle."
msgstr ""
"At one time, mendicants, I was staying near Ukkaṭṭhā, in the Subhaga Forest "
"at the root of a magnificent <i>sal</i> tree."

msgctxt "dn14:199.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr "As I was in private solitude this thought came to mind: "

#. VAR: anāvutthapubbo → anaj­jhā­vuttha­pubbo (bj) | anaj­jhā­vuṭṭha­pubbo
#. (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:199.3"
msgid ""
"‘na kho so sattāvāso sulabharūpo, yo mayā anāvutthapubbo iminā dīghena "
"addhunā aññatra suddhāvāsehi devehi."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s not easy to find any realm that I haven’t previously dwelt in in all "
"this long time, except with the gods of the pure abodes."

msgctxt "dn14:199.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena suddhāvāsā devā tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I go to see them?’"

msgctxt "dn14:199.5"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ "
"pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm,"

msgctxt "dn14:199.6"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:199.7"
msgid ""
"ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ subhagavane sālarājamūle antarahito avihesu devesu pāturahosiṃ."
msgstr "I vanished from the Subhaga Forest and reappeared with the Aviha gods."

msgctxt "dn14:199.8"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni "
"devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"In that order of gods, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands of deities "
"approached me,"

msgctxt "dn14:199.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr "bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn14:199.10"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and said to me:"

msgctxt "dn14:199.11"
msgid ""
"‘ito so, mārisā, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke udapādi."
msgstr ""
"‘Ninety-one eons ago, good sir, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, "
"perfected and fully awakened."

msgctxt "dn14:199.12"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, "
"khattiyakule udapādi."
msgstr "He was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family."

msgctxt "dn14:199.13"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi."
msgstr "Koṇḍañña was his clan."

msgctxt "dn14:199.14"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asītivassasahassāni "
"āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "He lived for 80,000 years."

msgctxt "dn14:199.15"
msgid ""
"Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle abhisambuddho."
msgstr "He was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree."

msgctxt "dn14:199.16"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma "
"sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "He had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa."

msgctxt "dn14:199.17"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ."
msgstr "He had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:199.18"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ."
msgstr "one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:199.19"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:199.20"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn14:199.21"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ "
"sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements."

msgctxt "dn14:199.22"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma bhikkhu "
"upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "He had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka."

msgctxt "dn14:199.23"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma rājā "
"pitā ahosi."
msgstr "His father was King Bandhuma,"

msgctxt "dn14:199.24"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī,"

msgctxt "dn14:199.25"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī."

# This is basically a table of contents for any Buddha biography.
msgctxt "dn14:199.26"
msgid ""
"Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ "
"ahosi evaṃ pabbajjā evaṃ padhānaṃ evaṃ abhisambodhi evaṃ "
"dhammacakkappavattanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And such was his renunciation, such his going forth, such his striving, such "
"his awakening, and such his rolling forth of the wheel of Dhamma."

msgctxt "dn14:199.27"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ, mārisā, vipassimhi bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu "
"kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti …"
msgstr ""
"And good sir, after leading the spiritual life under that Buddha Vipassī we "
"lost interest in desire for sensual pleasures and were reborn here.’"

# While this is absent here, they are all mentioned below, and comm says they should be included here. This must be just a clumsy abbreviation.
msgctxt "dn14:199.28"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"And other deities came and similarly recounted the details of the Buddhas "
"Sikhī, Vessabhū, Kakusandha, Koṇāgamana, and Kassapa."

# In PTS, unlike MS, the deities who came to see the Buddha are numbered as "hundreds", which seems more reasonable. RD has this, while MW does not.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="179"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.30"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.52"></a>
msgctxt "dn14:200.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃyeva kho, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni "
"devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "In that order of gods, many hundreds of deities approached me,"

msgctxt "dn14:200.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr "bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn14:200.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and said to me:"

msgctxt "dn14:200.4"
msgid ""
"‘imasmiṃyeva kho, mārisā, bhaddakappe bhagavā etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"loke uppanno."
msgstr ""
"‘In the present fortunate eon, good sir, you have arisen in the world, "
"perfected and fully awakened."

msgctxt "dn14:200.5"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, khattiyo jātiyā khattiyakule uppanno."
msgstr "You were born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family."

msgctxt "dn14:200.6"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, gotamo gottena."
msgstr "Gotama is your clan."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn14:200.7"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato, mārisā, appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ yo ciraṃ jīvati, so "
"vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"For you the life-span is short, brief, and fleeting. A long-lived person "
"lives for a century or a little more."

msgctxt "dn14:200.8"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, assatthassa mūle abhisambuddho."
msgstr "You were awakened at the root of a peepul tree."

msgctxt "dn14:200.9"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato, mārisā, sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ "
"bhaddayugaṃ."
msgstr "You have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

msgctxt "dn14:200.10"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato, mārisā, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni."
msgstr "You have had one gathering of disciples—1,250 "

msgctxt "dn14:200.11"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato, mārisā, ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva "
"khīṇāsavānaṃ."
msgstr "mendicants who had ended their defilements."

msgctxt "dn14:200.12"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, ānando nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko."
msgstr "You have as chief attendant a mendicant named Ānanda."

msgctxt "dn14:200.13"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, suddhodano nāma rājā pitā ahosi."
msgstr "Your father is King Suddhodana,"

msgctxt "dn14:200.14"
msgid "Māyā nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti."
msgstr "your birth mother was Queen Māyā,"

msgctxt "dn14:200.15"
msgid "Kapilavatthu nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi."
msgstr "and your capital city was Kapilavatthu.”"

msgctxt "dn14:200.16"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato, mārisā, evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ ahosi evaṃ pabbajjā evaṃ padhānaṃ "
"evaṃ abhisambodhi evaṃ dhammacakkappavattanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And such was your renunciation, such your going forth, such your striving, "
"such your awakening, and such your rolling forth of the wheel of Dhamma."

msgctxt "dn14:200.17"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ, mārisā, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ "
"virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And good sir, after leading the spiritual life under you we lost interest in "
"desire for sensual pleasures and were reborn here.’"

